f 66 galaxies per arcmin^2, the final\nCOSMOS weak lensing catalog contains 3.9x10^5 galaxies with accurate shape\nmeasurements. The properties of the COSMOS weak lensing catalog described\nthroughout this paper will provide key input numbers for the preparation and\ndesign of next-generation wide field space missions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Feb 2007 23:44:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
