 the magnetic stresses ${\\cal L}_M$. While the sum of\nthe angular momentum fluxes ${\\cal L}_P={\\cal L}_p+{\\cal L}_\\alpha$ of both\nspecies is found to be smaller than the magnetic stress ${\\cal L}_M$, for the\nfast and slow wind alike, this result is at variance with the Helios\nmeasurements.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Feb 2007 14:54:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Mar 2007 11:37:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-02-11"}
